sense.name: be vexed or worry (about)
sense.examples: Don't fret over these details. Experts are fretting over online extortion attempts. Amanda fretted him with her constant sighing. It frets her to be kept in the dark. Janet frets her breasts are too small. Chris fretted, 'What if we don't make it in time?'

sense.name: cause friction; wear away or erode
sense.examples: The seal design is fretting the shaft, causing a leak path through the damaged sleeve.

sense.name: press the string and fret of an instrument to create a note
sense.examples: You could mute the G string by slightly angling the finger that is fretting the D string. Many guitarists apply too much pressure when fretting the strings.

sense.name: provide a musical instrument with frets
sense.examples: Here are some tips on fretting your guitar, including removing old frets.

sense.name: carve or decorate with an interlaced design
sense.examples: The fretwork was exquisite, although the columns have seldom been fretted along the base.
